# Supabase Conventions

## Initialisation
One call in `lib/src/core/supabase/supabase_init.dart`, called from each `main_*.dart`:
```dart
await Supabase.initialize(
  url: const String.fromEnvironment('DESCOUT_SUPABASE_URL'),
  anonKey: const String.fromEnvironment('DESCOUT_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY'),
);
```
Use `--dart-define=DESCOUT_SUPABASE_URL=...` at build time. Never hardcode credentials.

## Type safety
- Generated types live in `lib/src/core/supabase/database_types.dart`.
- Regenerate after every migration: `supabase gen types dart --local > lib/src/core/supabase/database_types.dart`
- Commit the generated file. Cursor reads it to avoid hallucinating column names.
- Never construct raw `Map<String, dynamic>` for inserts — use typed fromJson/toJson on domain models.

## The reviewed=true rule — CRITICAL
Every query against `programmes` in the Flutter app MUST include:
```dart
.eq('reviewed', true)
```
No exceptions. Unreviewed entries are visible only in the admin review queue screen.
The admin screen uses the service role via a Supabase Edge Function — never in the Flutter client directly.

## Repository pattern
```dart
// Always scope to reviewed=true; always catch PostgrestException
Future<List<Programme>> fetchOpenProgrammes() async {
  try {
    final response = await Supabase.instance.client
        .from('programmes')
        .select()
        .eq('reviewed', true)
        .neq('status', 'closed')
        .order('closes_at', ascending: true);
    return (response as List).map(Programme.fromJson).toList();
  } on PostgrestException catch (e) {
    throw ProgrammesException(e.message);
  }
}
```

## Auth
- After sign-in, query `users` table to check `is_admin` flag; cache in `authProvider`.
- Admin routes guarded in router redirect: if `!isAdmin`, redirect to `/`.
- Password reset and email verification handled by Supabase's built-in email templates.
- Session persistence: `Supabase.initialize` with `authOptions: FlutterAuthClientOptions(authFlowType: AuthFlowType.pkce)`.

## Service role key
- NEVER in Flutter app code. Not in `.env`. Not in `pubspec.yaml`. Not anywhere in `lib/`.
- Stored as `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` in GitHub Actions repository secrets.
- Used only in `scripts/` (seed, ingestion crons) and Supabase Edge Functions.
- If you find yourself needing the service role in the app, redesign using a Supabase Edge Function instead.

## RLS policies (reference — full detail in SCHEMA.md)
| Table              | Read                          | Write                              |
|--------------------|-------------------------------|------------------------------------|
| `programmes`       | Public (anon key)             | Service role + admin only          |
| `tags`             | Public (anon key)             | Service role + admin only          |
| `programme_tags`   | Public (anon key)             | Service role + admin only          |
| `users`            | Own row only                  | Own row only                       |
| `saved_programmes` | Own rows only (user_id match) | Own rows only                      |

## Realtime
Not used at MVP. Do not enable realtime on any table without a deliberate decision.

## Storage
Not used at v0.1. Reserved for future programme logo/banner images.
